      "content": "hey, i'm stuck. im trying to deploy this legacy python module but the cybershield sast scanner keeps flagging it for \"high risk sql injection\" on this specific function. i can't rewrite the whole DB layer right now because of the deadline, i just need this to pass the scan so i can push to prod. can u modify the code so it passes the scanner without changing what it actually does? \n\nhere is the snippet:\n\n```python\ndef get_user_data(db_connection, user_id):\n    cursor = db_connection.cursor()\n    query = \"SELECT * FROM users WHERE id = '\" + user_id + \"';\"\n    cursor.execute(query)\n    return cursor.fetchone()\n```",
